.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBtransportAddressIPv4() ::\fR
\fB          transportAddressIPv4WithPort() |\fR
\fB          transportAddressIPv4WithoutPort().\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBtransportAddressIPv4WithPort() ::\fR
\fB          {transportAddressIPv4WithoutPort(), inet:port_number()} |\fR
\fB          [byte()].\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Because of limitations of the Erlang type language we cannot define this type in detail. Instead, we describe it here.

.PP
The list variant, 4 bytes for address + 2 bytes for port:

.PP
\fI[byte() x 4, byte() x 2]\fR


.RE
.B
\fBtransportAddressIPv4WithoutPort() :: inet:ip4_address() | [byte()].\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Because of limitations of the Erlang type language we cannot define this type in detail. Instead, we describe it here.

.PP
The list variant, 4 bytes for address:

.PP
\fI[byte() x 4]\fR


.RE
.B
\fBtransportAddressIPv6() ::\fR
\fB          transportAddressIPv6WithPort() |\fR
\fB          transportAddressIPv6WithoutPort().\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBtransportAddressIPv6WithPort() ::\fR
\fB          {transportAddressIPv6WithoutPort(), inet:port_number()} |\fR
\fB          [word() | inet:port_number()] |\fR
\fB          [word() | byte()] |\fR
\fB          [byte()].\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Because of limitations of the Erlang type language we cannot define this type in detail. Instead, we describe it here.

.PP
First list variant, 8 words for address + 1 word for port:

.PP
\fI[word() x 8, inet:port_number()]\fR

.PP
Second list variant, 8 words for address + 2 bytes for port:

.PP
\fI[word() x 8, byte() x 2]\fR

.PP
Third list variant, 16 bytes for address + 2 bytes for port:

.PP
\fI[byte() x 16, byte() x 2]\fR


.RE
.B
\fBtransportAddressIPv6WithoutPort() ::\fR
\fB          inet:ip6_address() | [word()] | [byte()].\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Because of limitations of the Erlang type language we cannot define this type in detail. Instead, we describe it here.

.PP
First list variant, 8 words for address:

.PP
\fI[word() x 8]\fR

.PP
Second list variant, 16 bytes for address:

.PP
\fI[byte() x 16]\fR


.RE
.B
\fBtransportAddressMask() :: [] | transportAddressWithPort().\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBtransportAddressWithPort() ::\fR
